cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on video classification using both visual and audio modalities, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimodal learning (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of factorized bilinear pooling, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on a large-scale dataset, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
